# Inclusio — Cursor rule

This repository (or a sibling content repo) is built by the
[Inclusio](https://github.com/sebastienrousseau/inclusio)
engine. When editing `.tex`, `.cls`, `.sty`, or `data/meta.yaml`, prefer
the engine's CLI over hand-running `latexmk`.

## Core commands

```bash
python -m inclusio.cli.build list                          # enumerate
python -m inclusio.cli.build build --mode camera-ready     # build all
python -m inclusio.cli.audit --strict                      # EAA gate
python -m inclusio.cli.render --doc cv --format text       # ATS .txt
```

`make publish CONTENT_DIR=/path/to/content/repo` for split-repo layouts.

## Tagged PDF preamble (MANDATORY for camera-ready)

```latex
\DocumentMetadata{
  pdfversion   = 2.0,
  pdfstandard  = ua-2,
  pdfstandard  = a-4f,
  lang         = en-GB,
  testphase    = {phase-III, table, math, sec-latex},
}
\documentclass[final,tagged]{pub-<class>}
```

`\DocumentMetadata` MUST precede `\documentclass`. Omitting `[tagged]`
defaults to untagged (which fails the EAA gate). Use `[final-untagged]`
as an explicit opt-out — never just remove `[tagged]`.

## Avoid these untagged-content traps (veraPDF rule §8.2.2)

- `\maketitle` on pub-paper/arxiv/preprint emits untagged rules → omit
  or use class-specific title macros.
- `\titleformat[\titlerule]` on pub-cv/pub-faq → use class semantic
  macros, not raw `\section{...}`.
- `\linenumbers` on pub-preprint → call `\nolinenumbers` for tagged.

## Forbidden commands inside the document body

`chktex` + the semantic-check script reject:
`\textbf`, `\textit`, `\vspace`, `\hspace`, `\fontsize`, `\color{`,
`\centering` (except inside `figure` / `table` / `minipage` floats).

Use `\emph`, the class's spacing controls, and the `cv-section`-family
macros instead.

## MCP server

`pip install 'inclusio[mcp]'` then `inclusio-mcp` exposes the engine
as an MCP server with tools `list_docs`, `audit_pdf`, `render`,
`doc_count` and resources `inclusio://meta`, `inclusio://audit/latest`,
`inclusio://version`. Use it when the agent needs structured access to the
manifest or audit reports rather than shelling out.

